{"id": "EUVD-2022-34781", "enisaUuid": "1368eedb-bb78-3e31-aaf1-4de60a074049", "description": "A use-after-free vulnerability was found in systemd. This issue occurs due to the on_stream_io() function and dns_stream_complete() function in 'resolved-dns-stream.c' not incrementing the reference counting for the DnsStream object. Therefore, other functions and callbacks called can dereference the DNSStream object, causing the use-after-free when the reference is still used later.", "datePublished": "2022-09-09T00:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-03T00:39:08", "baseScore": 9.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2022-2526.html", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:6160", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:6161", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:6162", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:6163", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2022-2526", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:6206", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:6551", "https://github.com/systemd/systemd/commit/d973d94dec349fb676fdd844f6fe2ada3538f27c", "https://security.netapp.com/advisory/ntap-20221111-0005/"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-2526"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 0.25, "enisaIdProduct": [], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "e22c5144-00e1-3ef8-8f80-cf5998f2b0c7", "vendor": {"name": "n/a"}}], "isExploited": false}